      "description": "**Forming Boarding Squads**\nThe following units do not split into separate units in the Form Boarding Squads step:\n- ^^**Hormagaunts**^^\n- ^^**Neurogaunts**^^\n- ^^**Termagants**^^\n\n**Mustering A Boarding Patrol**\nYou can include up to two of the following unit:\n- **^^Winged Tyranid Prime^^**\n\nYou can include up to two of the following units:\n- **^^Tyranid Warriors with Melee Bio-weapons^^** (3 models)\n- **^^Tyranid Warriors with Ranged Bio-weapons^^** (3 models)\n\nYou can include up to one of each of the following units:\n- **^^Hormagaunts^^** (10 models)\n- **^^Neurogaunts^^** (10 models)\n- **^^Ripper Swarms^^** (3 models)\n- **^^Termagants^^** (10 models)\n\n**Rules Adaptions**\n- **^^Endless Multitude^^** and **^^Ripper Swarms^^** units from your army are ignored for the purposes of determining visibility for friendly **^^Tyranids^^** models that do not have the **^^Endless Multitude^^** or **^^Ripper Swarms^^** keyword.\n- You can give the Tyranid Prime models in **^^Tyranid Warriors with Melee Bio-weapons^^**  and **^^Tyranid Warriors with Ranged Bio-weapons^^** units Enhancements as if they were **^^Character^^** models.\n- **^^Tyranid Warriors with Melee Bio-weapons^^** and **^^Tyranid Warriors with Ranged Bio-weapons^^** units can perform the Secure Site Tactical Manoeuvre as if they had the **^^Battleline^^** keyword.\n- **^^Endless Multitude^^** units cannot perform the Secure Site Tactical Manoeuvre.\n- The **^^Ripper Swarms^^** unit loses the Deep Strike ability.\n- The **^^Termagants^^** unit loses the Skulking Horrors ability.\n- The **^^Winged Tyranid Prime^^** model loses the Deep Strike ability.\n\n**Xeno-Terror**\nWhen you unleash the Shadow in the Warp, subtract 1 from the Battle-shock test each enemy unit on the battlefield must take as a result. For each enemy unit that fails one of those tests, that enemy unit cannot Fire Overwatch this turn.\n\n**Synaptic Web**\nUnits from your army with the Shadow in the Warp ability retain that ability.\n\nUnits from your army with the Synapse ability retain that ability and gain this one.\n\nWhen measuring whether a unit from your army is within Synapse Range of a friendly **^^Synapse^^** model, Walls and closed Hatchways are ignored."
